MEASLES - DAGESTAN
******************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 9 Feb 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Interfax News Agency, Thu 5 Feb 2004 (translated from Russian by
Mod.NR) [edited]
<http://www.interfax.ru/r/B/0/182.html?menu=35&id_issue=8182514>

Dagestan: outbreak of measles in the capital
--------------------------------------------
According to the Interfax News Agency, an outbreak of measles has occurred
in Mahachkala (the capital city of Dagestan). Since the beginning of
January 2004, 355 people have been registered as measles cases. 100 of them
are children under 14 years old. The largest numbers of cases were recorded
in the following villages: Hasvyurt, Kaytar, Unzukulsk, and Mahachkala.
Specialists from the sanitary epidemiological surveillance center are
conducting vaccination in the focus of infection.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The involvement of adults and young children in the outbreak suggests
either a breakdown in vaccination routine or something unusual. Further
information would be appreciated. - Mod.CP]
